The paper deals with training generative neural networks to generate images of objects, specifically chairs, tables, and cars. This involves using convolutional networks to learn a meaningful representation of 3D models, which suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper involves inventing new objects not present in the training set, which suggests that it may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also deals with finding correspondences between different objects from the dataset, which suggests that it may fall under the graphics (cs.GR) category. Finally, the paper involves training neural networks, which suggests that it may also fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
